{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":175085,"duration_api_ms":174413,"num_turns":10,"result":"## Code Review — `task-1` on `feature/issue-17`\n\n**Result: `changes_requested`**\n\nThe rewrite of `test-integration.bats` is a genuine improvement — it removes 162 lines of stale stage references and replaces them with 358 lines of well-structured tests tracking the current pipeline. Coverage spans all 8 stages with good mix of structural and behavioral assertions.\n\nFive minor issues need to be addressed:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Redundant `result=$?` pattern in M/L quality loop tests (lines 279–290) — *Minor*\nTests for M-size and L-size don't use `run`, so `$?` is always `0` if execution reaches that line. The `[ \"$result\" -eq 0 ]` check is tautological. Use the same pattern as the S-size test:\n```bash\nrun should_run_quality_loop \"M\"\n[ \"$status\" -eq 0 ]\n```\n\n### 2. Same anti-pattern in docs stage test (lines 749–754) — *Minor*\nThe typescript variant uses `$?` capture while the bash/config variants correctly use `run` + `$status`. Fix for consistency:\n```bash\nrun should_run_docs_stage \"typescript\"\n[ \"$status\" -eq 0 ]\n```\n\n### 3. Misleading test name at line 383 — *Minor*\n`\"detect_change_scope classifies typescript files\"` — the body only checks `type -t detect_change_scope` (existence), no classification is tested. Either rename to `\"detect_change_scope function exists\"` or remove (the function's behavior is covered in `test-smart-test-targeting.bats`).\n\n### 4. Overly broad exit assertions (lines 507–534) — *Minor*\n`\"orchestrator exits 1 on parse_issue failure\"` and `\"orchestrator exits 2 on max PR review iterations\"` both match `exit 1`/`exit 2` anywhere in the full `main` function body — they'd still pass if the specific exit path were removed. Consider narrowing context or remove in favour of the behavioral tests lower in the file.\n\n### 5. Duplicate schema copy in `setup()` (lines 28–29) — *Minor*\n`setup_